The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	Thrissur, Aug 26 (PTI): A tippler who had downed one too many and had a sound sleep in a hospital mortuary frightened women staff who saw him rising from the inquest table when they came to fetch a stretcher to move in a cadaver.           
	The incident occurred at the Government Medical College Hospital here three days ago. The drunken man had got down at the railway station and taken an auto after he realised it was not his destination. The driver, after drinking with him, took him to the hospital compound and told him it was a workshop where he could sleep undisturbed. The man, an employee of a private firm in Malappuram district, was let off after a case was registered for trespassing, police said.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): A Delhi court has granted bail to a suspected Lashkar-e-Toiba militant accused of providing money to the alleged mastermind of the Diwali-eve blasts here in 2005. During the arguments, Gulam Ahmed Khans counsel contended that the accused had already spent five years in jail, equivalent to the term prescribed under law.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Property statements filed by civil servants are not confidential information and can be disclosed under the RTI Act after taking the views of the officials concerned, the Central Information Commission has held.                   
	Houston (PTI): The immigration bail hearing of Indian documentary filmmaker Vijay Kumar, who was detained at an airport here for carrying a weapon in his baggage, has been shifted to September 2. Kumars passport is still with the authorities.                                                                                                                                              
